"""Final 4-method comparison against two HCR target binaries.

Methods (all initialised by the same FFT-NCC θ-sweep rigid stage):
  M1 rigid               — translation + rotation only.
  M2 rigid + affine      — 4-DOF similarity, scale ±15 %, θ ±15°.
  M4a rigid + PWR 3×3    — Suite2p-style piecewise rigid on binary.
  M4b rigid + PWR 4×4    — same, finer block grid.

HCR targets (both rendered on the level-4 pia-flat 0–100 µm grid):
  A. ws488 — watershed-binarised HCR 488 MIP (current).
  B. gfp_roi — GFP+ HCR cell-body ROI disks (radius ≈ 5 µm) projected
     from ``s.hcr_centroids`` filtered by ``s.hcr_gfp_df``, depth-
     filtered to [0, 100] µm beneath the HCR top surface.

Protocol:
  1. Run M1 on FULL HCR canvas (independently per target).
  2. Crop HCR to bbox of M1 mapping + 15 % margin → cropped frame.
  3. Run M2/M4a/M4b on the cropped frame.
  4. NCC = binary-vs-binary on the cropped frame, single mask, for
     every method.
  5. For each subject report the best of {M1, M2, M4a, M4b} per
     target.

Outputs:
  • figures/compare_methods_final_{sid}.png — 2×5 panel per subject
    (rows = target ws488 / gfp_roi, cols = HCR / M1 / M2 / M4a / M4b)
  • figures/compare_methods_final_summary.png — grouped bar chart
  • compare_methods_final_summary.json
"""
